{# Shared visual contract — included at the top of every section prompt. #}
You are creating section {{ section_number }} of 8 of a VERTICAL portrait
landing-page banner for {{ brief.name }}{% if brief.brand %} by {{ brief.brand }}{% endif %}.

Subject (must appear, photoreal, visually integrated into the scene):
  - {{ brief.name }} ({{ brief.category }}{% if brief.sub_category %} / {{ brief.sub_category }}{% endif %})
  - The product packaging in reference image #1 is the EXACT subject — keep
    its label, colors, shape, and proportions faithful.

Visual identity:
  - Palette: {{ palette_str }}.
  - Mood: {{ style_keywords }}.
  - Editorial GCC (Khaleeji) aesthetic. Warm, premium, modern.
  - NO embedded text, NO logos other than the product's own, NO watermarks.
  - NO flat solid-color backgrounds — always rich texture, depth, gradients.

Composition: 1024×1536 portrait, 2:3 ratio. {{ section_role }}

{% if seamless_top %}
SEAMLESS TOP EDGE (critical):
  Reference image #2 is the BOTTOM strip of the PREVIOUS section. The TOP
  edge of THIS image MUST visually continue from that strip: same dominant
  colors at the top, matching texture and lighting, so when stacked the seam
  is invisible. Treat reference #2 as the literal pixels that sit above the
  top of your canvas.
{% else %}
SEAMLESS TOP EDGE:
  This is section 1 — the top of the image sets the visual tone for the
  entire page. Make the top edge a clean, branded gradient/texture that
  the next section can pick up.
{% endif %}

SEAMLESS BOTTOM EDGE:
  Leave the BOTTOM ~20% of the image as a calm gradient or texture (no
  prominent subject, no text region), so the next section's top edge can
  blend in cleanly.

Save the bottom 256 px for the seam — keep it visually quiet.
